{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Against the ever-growing influx of textual content, being able to effectively summarize long pieces of text is crucial to extract useful information.",
    "Whereas once a significant amount of manual labour would be necessary, now automatic text summarization (ATS) can be performed by deep learning models, especially as they grow in capabilities and become more easily accessible (Bubeck et al., 2023).",
    "Nevertheless, such deep learning models are essentially black boxes.",
    "They provide no immediate information regarding their internals, and they can fail in ways imperceptible to a novice, e.g.",
    "by producing incorrect output that looks legitimate and create an illusion of understanding (Messeri and Crockett, 2024; Li, 2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Whereas once a significant amount of manual labour would be necessary, now automatic text summarization (ATS) can be performed by deep learning models, especially as they grow in capabilities and become more easily accessible (Bubeck et al., 2023).",
    "by producing incorrect output that looks legitimate and create an illusion of understanding (Messeri and Crockett, 2024; Li, 2023)."
  ]
